01:56:17,813 --> 01:56:19,280
[DOOR CREAKING]

626
01:56:57,453 --> 01:56:58,186
[SIGHS]

627
01:57:30,553 --> 01:57:32,153
MAN:
Dominic?

628
01:57:35,357 --> 01:57:36,658
Dominic Matei?

629
01:57:39,495 --> 01:57:43,131
<i>Cuconul Dominic Matei?</i>

630
01:57:46,135 --> 01:57:48,136
Is it you?

631
01:57:53,075 --> 01:57:54,909
Praise God,

632
01:57:54,910 --> 01:57:57,278
you've returned.

633
01:57:57,279 --> 01:58:00,381
Dr. Neculache, look.
He's back.

634
01:58:02,585 --> 01:58:06,154
<i>Cuconul Dominic is here.</i>

635
01:58:06,155 --> 01:58:07,388
<i>DOMINIC:</i>
<i>In other words,</i>

636
01:58:07,389 --> 01:58:09,657
<i>the story begins</i>
<i>all over again.</i>

637
01:58:09,658 --> 01:58:11,559
Old friend.

638
01:58:11,560 --> 01:58:12,927
Dominic?

639
01:58:12,928 --> 01:58:14,662
Look, it's you.
- I'm dreaming.

640
01:58:14,663 --> 01:58:16,364
I am dreaming.

641
01:58:16,365 --> 01:58:17,665
When I wake up,

642
01:58:17,666 --> 01:58:21,569
it will seem like
I've just begun to dream indeed.

643
01:58:21,570 --> 01:58:23,104
It's like, uh,

644
01:58:23,105 --> 01:58:27,275
the story of Chuang-tzu
and the butterfly.

645
01:58:27,276 --> 01:58:29,778
The story of Chuang-tzu
and the butterfly?

646
01:58:29,779 --> 01:58:30,578
[SIGHING]
Yes.

647
01:58:32,848 --> 01:58:36,885
A king who was dreaming
that he was a butterfly

648
01:58:36,886 --> 01:58:39,120
that dreamed he was a king,

649
01:58:39,121 --> 01:58:40,989
who was dreaming
he was a butterfly.

650
01:58:40,990 --> 01:58:43,758
I know very well
that I'm--

651
01:58:43,759 --> 01:58:45,026
I'm dreaming,

652
01:58:45,027 --> 01:58:48,096
and in a minute or two
I will wake up.

653
01:58:48,097 --> 01:58:50,765
<i>You are awake, Cucoane Dominic,</i>

654
01:58:50,766 --> 01:58:52,300
but you are tired.

655
01:58:52,301 --> 01:58:55,170
In fact, you look very tired.

656
01:58:55,171 --> 01:58:56,171
All right.

657
01:58:56,172 --> 01:58:59,908
Between December the 20th, 1938,

658
01:58:59,909 --> 01:59:02,010
and this evening,
many things have happened.

659
01:59:02,011 --> 01:59:04,913
<i>That is when it is happening,</i>
<i>Cucoane Dominic.</i>

660
01:59:04,914 --> 01:59:07,582
This is December 20th, 1938.

661
01:59:07,583 --> 01:59:09,818
I don't dare tell you

662
01:59:09,819 --> 01:59:11,820
what year we are
really living in,

663
01:59:11,821 --> 01:59:14,956
we who are outside this dream.

664
01:59:14,957 --> 01:59:18,259
I know that if I were to make
the effort, I would wake up.

665
01:59:18,260 --> 01:59:20,628
<i>You are not dreaming,</i>
<i>Coane Dominic.</i>

666
01:59:20,629 --> 01:59:22,931
You're here with us,
your friends.

667
01:59:22,932 --> 01:59:25,100
You're at the Café Select.

668
01:59:25,101 --> 01:59:27,769
This is what we imagined
would happen.

669
01:59:27,770 --> 01:59:30,438
<i>When Conul Dominic</i>
<i>comes to his senses,</i>

670
01:59:30,439 --> 01:59:34,175
when he recovers,
you'll see.

671
01:59:34,176 --> 01:59:36,611
He'll go straight
to the Café Select.

672
01:59:36,612 --> 01:59:38,113
[SPEAKING
IN FOREIGN LANGUAGE]

673
01:59:38,114 --> 01:59:39,481
But if I'm not dreaming,

674
01:59:39,482 --> 01:59:42,517
then you'd know about...

675
01:59:42,518 --> 01:59:44,719
Hiroshima.

676
01:59:44,720 --> 01:59:47,021
Of the hydrogen bomb,

677
