the astronaut who landed

679
01:59:52,094 --> 01:59:53,595
and walked on the moon...

680
01:59:53,596 --> 01:59:54,662
[SNORTS]

681
01:59:54,663 --> 01:59:55,797
...last summer in July.

682
01:59:57,633 --> 01:59:59,134
MAN:
Dominic!

683
02:00:00,603 --> 02:00:02,771
Dominic, it's true.

684
02:00:02,772 --> 02:00:05,974
You've come back.

685
02:00:05,975 --> 02:00:08,042
Welcome.

686
02:00:08,043 --> 02:00:09,978
[MAN SINGING IN FOREIGN
LANGUAGE OVER RADIO]

687
02:00:18,187 --> 02:00:19,788
You look good.

688
02:00:19,789 --> 02:00:22,991
Welcome, old friend.

689
02:00:22,992 --> 02:00:27,061
It's like that story of, uh,
the Chinese philosopher,

690
02:00:27,062 --> 02:00:29,364
you know, the one
I've told you about many times.

691
02:00:29,365 --> 02:00:30,965
Which Chinese philosopher?

692
02:00:30,966 --> 02:00:34,536
The name escapes me now.

693
02:00:34,537 --> 02:00:36,271
The one with the butterfly.

694
02:00:39,875 --> 02:00:41,810
Well, it's too long to repeat.

695
02:00:41,811 --> 02:00:44,546
I'll call for a sleigh
to take you home.

696
02:00:44,547 --> 02:00:46,147
I don't need a sleigh.

697
02:00:48,117 --> 02:00:49,651
I'm going on foot.

698
02:00:53,289 --> 02:00:56,991
The next time
the problem arises,

699
02:00:56,992 --> 02:00:58,026
I shall know how to answer.

700
02:01:00,896 --> 02:01:03,198
What problem, dear Dominic?

701
02:01:09,071 --> 02:01:12,173
The problem which worries
all of us.

702
02:01:16,479 --> 02:01:18,480
[GASPS]
Dominic?

703
02:01:18,481 --> 02:01:20,281
Is it your teeth?

704
02:01:20,282 --> 02:01:22,250
Is it your teeth? Dominic?

705
02:01:39,502 --> 02:01:41,703
Should I lock up
the door?

706
02:01:41,704 --> 02:01:44,172
The guest in Room 19
hasn't come back yet.

707
02:01:44,173 --> 02:01:45,807
He went to the Café Select.

708
02:01:45,808 --> 02:01:47,075
I'll call.

709
02:01:50,146 --> 02:01:52,580
Yes, he came here.

710
02:01:52,581 --> 02:01:54,582
He went into the backroom.

711
02:01:54,583 --> 02:01:56,284
Uh, no one was there,

712
02:01:56,285 --> 02:01:58,052
so he stayed only
a few minutes

713
02:01:58,053 --> 02:02:00,421
and left without
saying good night.

714
02:02:00,422 --> 02:02:03,057
He was, uh, holding
his hand to his mouth.

715
02:02:11,967 --> 02:02:13,168
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

716
02:02:30,553 --> 02:02:32,487
[#]

717
02:03:17,266 --> 02:03:18,900
<i>VERONICA:</i>
<i>And the third?</i>

718
02:03:21,337 --> 02:03:22,937
<i>Where do you want me to put</i>

719
02:03:22,938 --> 02:03:25,573
<i>the third rose?</i>

